                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d632">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114A European War 1939/113: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-13T14:00:00+01:00"
                        >undated</date>.<lb/>[Received November 14, 1942—9 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1778. The following telegram has been sent to Tangier.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>November 13, 2 p.m. Your 573 to Department November 9, 11 p.m. British
                        Embassy in Madrid has obtained release and departure of British aviators
                        forced down in Spain and this Embassy will attempt to do likewise in similar
                        cases.</p>
                    <p>There is a possibility that American aviators now in Morocco might be
                        released if you make representation to that end. If not suggest you
                        telegraph following information to me: name in full, branch of service, rank
                        and serial numbers.</p>
                    <p>Repeated to Department.</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
